ng"=20
width=3D15></A></DIV>Ring of light is on!</DIV></DIV></DIV></DIV>
<P>Notice how the "1" indicator light turns on to show which controller =
is=20
assigned as player 1. Just like the Xbox 360, there can only be 4 Xbox =
360=20
controllers connected at the same time. DirectInput can supposedly =
support 52,=20
but I can't even imagine the wires involved with that.&nbsp;:) Right now =
i'm=20
doing a little hand waving with the "player 1" concept. Just understand =
that=20
each controller gets assigned a number automatically and you can use =
this number=20
to check the status of the controller (which buttons are pressed, what =
the left=20
thumbstick position is, etc.). </P>
<P>Now I'm going to remove the controller again. The program has been =
running=20
this whole time. </P>
<DIV class=3Dcenter>
<DIV class=3D"thumb tnone">
<DIV class=3Dthumbinner style=3D"WIDTH: 182px"><A class=3Dimage=20
title=3D"Detecting removal"=20
